  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The use of ultrasonography in detecting giant cell arteritis ( GCA) is emerging. Currently,
      temporal biopsy is the gold standard to diagnose GCA but studies have shown the interest to
      use B mode ultrasonography. However, until now, the study of velocities in GCA have not been
      yet performed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
